@rhatdan I hope that's not entirely true.  Brent's skimmed through things, giusseppe's implemented a new check, and either Adrian or Valentine (can't remember) did some fixup work on CRIU.  It's big to be sure, but I've tried my best to adopt POLA best I can.

@edsantiago It's simpler than travis and maybe even than papr.  The [entire ``.cirrus.yml`` documentation fits on one page](https://cirrus-ci.org/guide/writing-tasks/).  I've also [documented an overview of each task](https://github.com/containers/libpod/tree/master/contrib/cirrus).

*Bottom line:* If there's something not understandable or confusing, please let me know so I can document it :smile:
